HEADWORD: Snath
<hw>Snath</hw> <pr>(sn⟦acr⟧th)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. AS.
<ets>sn⟦imac⟧⟦edh⟧an</ets> to cut, to mow, <ets>sn⟦aemac⟧d</ets> a bite,
bit, snip.]</ety> <def>The handle of a scythe; a snead.</def>
<altsp>[Variously written in England <asp>snead</asp>, <asp>sneed</asp>,
<asp>sneath</asp>, <asp>sneeth</asp>, <asp>snathe</asp>, etc.; in
Scotland written <asp>sned</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

